<div type="definition">
<p>OBEY ENDURINGLY AND NOT OFFEND one's OWNER, as an ANIMAL, so as NOT to be WILD.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current word for tameness is xún 馴 (ant. jué 倔 "stubbornly insubordinate").</p>
<p>2. Fú 服 "submit" (ant. jiàng 強 "headstrong") is sometimes used referring to animals becoming or being tame.</p>
        </div>
